    <p>The award-win­ning Sin­ga­porean au­thor will dis­cuss her 2013 novel, which is about a teenage girl who briefly dis­ap­pears from her house in the mid­dle of the night in 1971, only to re­turn a dif­fer­ent per­son, caus­ing fis­sures in her Pun­jabi Sikh fam­ily. Jaswal won the Syd­ney Morn­ing Her­ald’s Best Young Aus­tralian Nov­el­ist Award in 2014 and her sec­ond novel Su­gar­bread (2016) was a fi­nal­ist for the Epi­gram Books Fic­tion Prize and the Sin­ga­pore Lit­er­a­ture Prize.</p>
    <p>Zoom Thu, 8pm</p>
